ingredients.text: 1/4 cup Sake Or Mirin (a Japanese Rice Wine)
4.0 tbsp rice wine vinegar (see know-how below)
5 1/3 tablespoons sushi vinegar, or 5 1/3 tablespoons rice vinegar, 5 tablespoons sugar and 3 tablespoons
1 (4 to 6 ounce) piece sushi-grade tuna or salmon
cooked sushi rice 1 1/4 cups (6 oz/185 g)
toasted nori seaweed 1 sheet, about 7 by 8 inches (18 by 20 cm)
toasted sesame seeds 1 tablespoon, plus more for sprinkling
English cucumber 1/4, peeled and cut into thin matchsticks
carrot 1/2, peeled and cut into thin matchsticks
soy sauce and pickled ginger slices for serving (optional)
soy sauce and pickled ginger slices for serving (optional)
3/4 cups grated daikon radish (use the large holes of a box grater) packed
3/4 cups grated red radish (use the large holes of a box grater) packed
1/4 to 3/4 teaspoon wasabi paste (depending on your tolerance for heat)
1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon mirin (Japanese cooking wine)
1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon mirin (Japanese cooking wine)
2 carrots, peeled and cut lengthwise into quarters
1/2 cucumber, cut in half lengthwise, seeded, and cut into 1/4-inch-thick strips
1 two-inch-long piece daikon radish, about 2 inches in diameter, peeled and julienned
16 leaves red-leaf lettuce, such as Lolla Rossa
grated zest and juice of one orange
grated zest and juice of 1/2 lemon
2 tablespoons (raw) brown sugar (reg. sugar is ok too)
1 avocado, peeled, pitted, and thinly sliced
2 tbsp rice or white wine vinegar
sweet soy sauce (kecap manis), to serve
sweet soy sauce (kecap manis), to serve

recipe.label: Tuna Sushi Salad And Wasabi Avocado recipes

ingredients.text: 1 1/4 cups cooked brown rice (or a mix of brown and wild rice)
1 tablespoon pickled ginger, drained and shredded
1 tablespoon each black and white sesame seeds
1/2 sheet sushi nori, snipped into pieces (optional)
½ a small head of broccoli
120 g hot-smoked salmon, from sustainable sources
50 g pea shoots or 20 g cress
1 cup rice short grain rice (sushi rice) (cooked as directed)
1 avocado (stoned, scooped and cut into thin strips)
6 ounces very fresh sushi grade tuna, cut into small dice
4 tablespoons Japanese or good quality basic mayonnaise
small handful crisp radish sprouts – to garnish
